<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 19 at 4:28AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Light snow to move through Southwest MT today...
Periods of light snow will affect areas over Beaverhead County
this morning, while the snow moves eastward and will affect areas
over Madison and Gallatin counties late this morning and through
the afternoon hours.
Visibility could fall below one half mile at times and roadways
could become snow covered and slippery for a time this morning
over Beaverhead County as the snow moves through.
After 10 AM, snowfall will generally melt on pavement surfaces.
Overall snow accumulations will generally range from 1 to 3 inches
in the higher valleys and at pass level, to about 3 to 6 inches
at ridge tops.</description>
